inn1.comm: on the length, a bit shorter if I may add and the batsman goes on to his back foot to defend, the ball barely comes on to the bat
short of length but this one gives him some room outside the off stump and he stands up tall, punches it but straight to the cover fielder
good length and quicker, bit of pace, back into the batsman and defended to mid-wicket
bouncer and a quick one at that! short of length and he jumps out of harm's way does Tamim!
short of length outside the off and punched to the off side, this time to the left of the cover fielder and they are off for the first run of the day
down the legs and it is glanced away through fine-leg for a four, the fielder was up in the circle and the bowler failed to change his line for the right-hander
outside the off and swinging into the batsman, driven to the off side but without too much timing
yorker length on the middle stump and defended to the on side, brings his bat down quickly on that one
gentle medium pace from Sammy, swings from the bowler's hand and the batsman has enough time to defend it back
short of length this time and Tamim is able to cut it away, not with full timing but enough to get him a single to the point fielder's right
squares him up with that one swinging away from the batsman, it was pitched right up to the bat and swung slightly away and the batsman was on the back foot defending it
pushed to mid-on and he wants a quick single, but Tamim sends him back and he is safely back home by the time the throw comes in to the keeper
short of length and on the off stump, defended on the back foot
short of length and it rears up out of nowhere! Where are we, Barbados, 1979? That has almost taken the batsman's head and the batsman is lucky not to fend it to the keeper!
on the back foot and defends that short of length ball again, a tad uncomfortably to the off side

and again, Tamim's living on the edge and it is all down to Rampaul's bowling here. The ball rises from length yet again and hits the shoulder of the bat, pops up to the off side and away from the point fielder
down the leg side for a wide, Rampaul was trying to dig it in but misses his line again to the right-hander
short of length on the off stump and he is quickly back and defends it to the left of the bowler
nothing in the batsman's half but this is probably expected by the batsman who is waiting on his back foot, guides it to third-man for a single
slower on the pads, definitely much slower than Rampaul, and it is neatly tucked away to deep square-leg for a couple of runs
poor ball, down the leg-side and the batsman lets that one go to allow the umpires to stretch his arms for a wide
gets the line and length right, gets it to swing away and beats the batsman outside the off stump, fuller, on off stump and beaten!
on a length, outside the off and allows it to go through to the keeper
another one on the off stump and that swing away again, defeats the batsman yet again, beats the outside edge
shortens his length and the batsman is on the back foot, defending at it
short of length but no swing on that one, tucked away to short fine-leg for a single
short of length and he tries to cut but does not get the middle of the bat

short of length and he goes for the hook, it was almost brilliantly taken by Bravo running to his left from the fine-leg region, but he floors it! That was a shot brought about by frustration of not scoring any runs...
short of length and defended on the back foot yet again
length ball outside the off stump and he is waiting on his back foot to push to the off
short of length, on the middle stump, pushed to mid-on
off stump line and slightly fuller, defended to the off side, getting back into the groove of respecting Rampaul after that rush of blood
short and wide outside the off stump and cut away, runs away to the fence before the fielder rushing towards it from third-man stops it...bit of a heavy outfield and the fielder slips
gets his line and length back against the right-hander, beaten outside the off, swinging away from the bat
on his pads this time and he will be unhappy to have flicked it straight to fine-leg, only for a single
on his pads and tucked away to the deep square-leg region, bit of swing back into the batsman
shortens his length slightly to the right-hander and he is immediately on his back foot to flick it away but straight to the square-leg fielder
on the back foot and defended back to the bowler
short of length and Tamim goes on to the back foot to try and punch it, but fails to get any timing on it and it rolls over to the leg side
poor ball on the leg stump line, it was a length ball too and easily flicked away to fine-leg, there was no fielder there, and the ball rolls over for four. There was a short fine-leg in place
outside the off and that is a sizzler! Punched through the covers, bisects the backward point and cover fielder to make it two in two!
sort of length and this time Tamim has his feet flying everywhere trying to fend at that one, it reared up again. Gets bit of a bat and is able to push it to the off side for a quick single
another bouncer and Anamul is going to go for another pull, but he misses it, through to the keeper
short of length ball on the middle stump and pushed back to the bowler
outside the off stump and fuller, driven straight to the extra-cover fielder, goes on the bounce
on the leg stump, with a bit of swing further down and flicked away to the deep square-leg
awkwardly defended to one on the off stump, inside edge to the mid-wicket region and he rushes off for a quick single...the fielder gets round quickly and has a shy but misses
short of length and pushed to the leg side for a single
on the leg stump to the right-hander this time and easily tapped away for a single
good line, good length and the batsman gets his bat and pad forward to defend it, and that is a good shot too. Not for runs though.
on the off stump, gets the batsman out, defends it to the off side
outside the off but very full, and it is driven through the covers for a four!
on the middle stump and a lot of turn but down the leg side and it is left alone by the batsman
on the off stump, fuller and the batsman brings his pad out forward to defend it to the leg side
quicker, bit of turn away and defended hurriedly to the leg side
slower on the middle and he tucks it away to the deep square-leg region for a single, slight bit of turn there
outside the off, lot of width for the batsman and it has been drilled but to the cover fielder
goes down the track to try and whip it to the leg-side but a leading edge almost goes back to the bowler
outside the off and tries to drive it, gets bit of an inside edge to the mid-on region
angles it into his pads, flicked away easily to mid-wicket and by the time the fielder gets to it, they are away for a couple
short of length and whacked away through mid-wicket, that is a shot of total confidence, of impetuousness, of disdain...
on the off and tapped away to deep square-leg for a single
over the wicket, fuller on middle and tapped away to mid-wicket
floated up on the off stump and he goes at it, misses hitting the middle and gets an inside edge
short of length and that is driven down the ground, to long-on for a single
quicker, shorter, on his pads and taps away to the leg side for a single
spinning away a tad and defended back to the bowler
fuller on the off and he brings his bat and pad together and defends
quicker on the middle and Anamul is on to his back foot, defends back to the right of the bowler
poor delivery, on his pads with no fine-leg on the boundary and it has been whipped away to the fence for a four by Tamim
this time on the off side, width and cut, but the fielder is at the deep point region and is able to cut it off, the ball goes to him too quickly and they can get only one
short of length to mid-wicket, Gayle bends to his right, picks it up and throws at the striker's stumps, misses, had he hit, the batsman was out of his crease, having being sent back by Tamim
short of length and defended to the leg side
short of length Sammy does not have any pace to test the batsman, Anamul goes for the hook and connects, goes over fine-leg for a biggie!
fuller and on the off, defended back to the bowler
on the off stump, opens the face of the bat and pushes it to the point region

tries to cut it away but edges it to the keeper! It was short and wide, and the shot was due but the bounce defeated him, there was a bit too much of it and Tamim fails to read that, a thin edge through to the keeper, one down after a good start
poor ball outside the off, short too deviating slightly away as well and easily cut away through the backward point region for a four

gone, two wickets in an over! He was trying to play it away to the leg side, too early to be playing that shot against a bowler of Narine's pedigree, gets a leading edge and it lobs up to the short cover region where the fielder back-pedals and takes it over his shoulder
short of length and the batsman's on his back foot, defended back
another one quicker on the off stump and Rahim defends it on his back foot
round the stumps, shorter and pushed away to his right, the bowler runs around to field
on the middle stump and defended
short of length and he is on the back foot, forces it to the square-leg
on the off stump, shorter and bit of spin away, defended on the back foot
shorter, quicker and he cuts it away to the deep point fielder
on the good length and the batsman's on the back foot, defends it to the leg side
short of length and the batsman's on the back foot, defends

out, gone, caught off a leading edge, but wait, is it a no-ball? Yes it is, yes it definitely is! It was on the off stump and turning away, bit of bounce and scoops it away to short cover, caught well but was over-stepping!
misses the stumping this time, but off a Free Hit! it was outside the off stump, very quick, almost swinging away, he went down the track, misses and so does the wicket-keeper

Gone this time, lbw! It was pitched fuller and the ball turned into the batsman, tries to defend it but misses the inside edge and hits the pads, the umpire has no hesitation in raising the finger and the cat's gone off his third life!
quicker and on a length, turning away from the batsman, beats the outside edge
shorter and crunched over mid-wicket for four by the new batsman! poor ball in the circumstances and the batsman is in good form, pulls it away
short yet again, outside the off and bit of turn away, pushes it to the covers and wants a single, but is sent back by the non-striker
outside the off and fuller, driven down the ground for a single
pitched right up, floated into the batsman who opens up to drive it through to long-off for a single
slower and what turn! grips on the off stump line and spins ferociously away, beats the outside edge
action replay of the previous one, turn away from the batsman and beats him again
this time he gets his front foot out further and defends well
on the off stump and pushed to the off side for a single
on the off stump, quicker and pushed to the off side for a single, deftly played
on the off and turn slightly into the bat, defends it back to the bowler
fuller on the middle and neatly driven down the ground for a single
outside the off and going further away...Rahim uses the pace and guides it through backward point for a couple of runs
on the middle stump and pushed it to the square-leg region
on the middle stump and pushed to the leg side, not for a run though

gone, caught at short-cover off a drive! It was on the off stump, stops on to the batsman and he fails to keep the drive down, the big frame of Pollard has to bend really low but he does that and is caught!
outside the off and defended back to the bowler
outside the off and quicker, goes for the cut and is lucky to not get an edge
outside the off, bit of turn into the bat, defended
fuller outside the off stump and driven through the covers for a single
short outside the off stump turning away from it and cut away to the deep point fielder for a single
on the off and defended to the right of the bowler
fuller and driven back to the bowler
tries to slow it down but it loses it line, down the leg side for a wide
another one on the leg stump and turn for Gayle, but down the leg-side
on the middle and Mushfiqur tries to work it away, gets bit of a leading edge but for a single
flights it up from round the stump, driven to short cover
yorker length and drilled back to the bowler

down the leg side for the left-hander this time and he goes for a sweep, misses, so does the keeper and the slip fielder who was rushing to his right to stop it, none of them succeed and it runs away.
goodness, what's he doing, another one down the leg side for a wide
flighted on the leg stump and swept away to deep square-leg for a single
down the pitch and he drives it through the extra-cover for a four, the fielder at mid-off and short cover were never getting their hand to it
slower on the off, bit of turn back and defended back to the bowler
quicker and fuller on the off stump, pushed to the off side but the keeper is quickly off towards the ball
shot, cut to one that is almost fuller, gets the outside edge through backward point for a four! The fielder there had to dive to his left but goes under it
shorter this time and he cuts it to the backward point fielder, who fumbles and they are away for a single
slower on the off stump and defended to the off side
short of length and bit of turn away, misses the outside edge defending it
fuller and flighted, defended it to the off side
slower and on the off stump, driven to long-off for a single, brings up the 100 of the innings
on his pads, wants to tap it away to the leg side but to the fielder it goes
fuller on the off and he drives it to mid-wicket
off stump line again and the batsman pats it on the front foot, off for a quick single
outside the off from round the stumps, drives it straight to short cover
quicker and down the leg side, lets it go through for a wide
flights it on his pads and he goes for a sweep, hits well but to the short fine-leg fielder
this is too short and too wide and Rahim's blade slashes at it hard, beats the fielder in the circle, beats one down at the fence and for a four
round the stump, angles in but without too much turn and he taps it to the leg side
slower and turns away from the bat, waits for the turn and opens the face of the bat, through the backward point region for three
down the wicket, the ball was turning in and it hits his pads, flies off to the off side but before the fielder can run in they are off for a leg-bye
slower now from round the stumps and defends it to the short mid-wicket
another one that is tossed up and the batsman defends it to the off side
outside the off from round the stumps and patted away to the off

gone, caught at short-cover! This is a tame dismissal, lack of experience probably, it was on the off stump and the batsman had played out three dots earlier, he went for a lavish drive and fails to keep it down, goes straight to the short-cover fielder
flighted on the off stump, works it away to the leg side
stump to stump, no turn and the new man defends it on his front foot, ends a maiden over that saw Gayle get a wicket too
outside the off stump from round the stumps, not too much turn and easily cut away to the deep point region for a single
round the stumps and drifts it down to the leg stump, taps it away for a quick single to get off the mark
quicker on the off stump and defended well by the skipper
fuller on the off and turning away, goes for a sweep and misses, the bounce seems to have done him there
shorter this time and he goes on to his back foot, punches it down to long-off for a single
on his pads, flicks it away to short fine-leg for a single
tries to cut it away but misses
plays it away to the leg side for a single
outside the off stump and taps it to the leg side
fuller on the off and flicked away to the leg side, but to the fielder
fuller on the off stump and drilled it through the covers for a single
slower this time and he brings out his front foot and defends to the off side
round the stumps and a lot of turn from there, almost turning square but the slowness of the delivery helps Tamim lets it go
shorter this but turn again, goes for a pre-meditated paddle sweep, the ball almost does not arrive but he adjusts well and gets a single
straighter on the off stump and defended back to the bowler
flighted up but on the leg stump, driven to short mid-wicket
on the middle, bit of turn and almost a leading edge while defending
quicker on the middle and this is well defended to the off side
down the leg side and a huge wide, lucky the keeper got his hand in the way
short of length from Gayle, on the back foot, bit of a bounce and defended to the off side
fuller on the middle and driven to long-on for a single
shorter outside off, and he wants to cut but does not go too hard at it
another one that is on the off stump with a bit of turn in, defended to short mid-wicket
short of length, he goes back and plays it away to the right of short mid-wicket for a single
very slow, very short but a lot of turn and he is only able to cut it away to deep point for a single
short of length outside the off and cuts it hard through backward point for a single
shorter from Polly and it angles into the bat, who lets it go, wide down the leg side
outside the off and too wide, is able to get his bat at it, cuts it to deep point
outside the off, slower and is able to open the face to guide it down to third-man for a single
fuller this time, outside the off and he leans into the drive, pushes it in the gap and by the time the deep point fielder can get close to the ball they are off for a couple
big, big appeal for lbw, but given not-out. It was slower and pitched and came into the batsman, hits him on his pads but was hitting outside the line of off
just a tad outside the off, slower and he plays it to third-man, they get a single and are able to rush back for the second, well run
wide, short and easily cut away to the backward point region for a four, it was quicker too
this time it is a tad fuller and he pushes it into the covers for a single
outside the off stump and he attempts a reverse sweep! why would he do that at this stage now? misses and hits his pads
bat and pad out and defends it back to the bowler
quicker on his pads and it is flicked away to the fine-leg region for a single
short of length but that is a lot of turn and it hits his thigh pad
goes down the track and that has been spanked over the deep mid-wicket region for a six!
and that is another one to the fence, but rather delicately! it was shorter and he was attempting the slower one, glances it to fine-leg for a four
short of length and tapped away to the leg side for a single
outside the off and length ball, tapped away to the covers for a quick single
short, wide and cut hard, but straight to the sweeper fielder
short of length and he was trying to guide it through third-man, gets it only to backward point
tries to cut it away, gets bit of an inside edge and goes to short fine-leg for a run
there is a lot of width on that one, cut away to deep point for a single
flighted on the off stump and he gets his bat out and defends it to the leg side
turn from outside the off, and goes down the leg side for a wide
on the off stump, tucked away to the square-leg
wants to cut it away, but misses the shot and goes through to the keeper
another wide down the leg-side, they have bowled too many of these this game
outside the off and pushed away to the off stump
short of length outside the off and pushes it to long-on for a single
short of a length on the off and bit of deviation away, taps it to the leg side
pitches it short again but not too much pace, outside off and the tap to the covers does not get him any run
short of length on the middle, he is on the back foot to defend it
fuller on the off and it is patted back to the bowler yet again, better for the West Indies
short of length and he is not making any attempt to score any...defended back to the bowler
outside the off and slower, cut away to the deep point region for a couple of runs
that was slower, he was going on to the back foot to steer it away, but the slowness of the ball defeats him
quicker and a yorker-length ball, dug out well by Rahim
goes down the track and drives it through the covers and almost beats the mid-off fielder who dives to this left and fields it
on the middle and defended to the leg side
fuller and driven down the ground for a single
fullish on the off stump and driven through to third-man for a single
fuller and outside off, swinging away from the batsman too and Rahim wanted to go for it before he lets it go
brings that one in, misses and it hits the pads, loud shout for lbw, but it seemed to have hit the pads high
wants to cut it away but gets an inside edge through to short fine-leg, quick single taken
on the off stump and defended back to the bowler
poor delivery, full-toss and on the legs of the batsman, flicked away to the deep square-leg region for an easy picking, 50-run stand for the sixth wicket, excellent one under pressure
middle stump line, fuller and flicked away to fine-leg for a single
defended on the front foot, he gets his foot forward and gets an inside edge to short fine-leg
on the off stump and patted away to the leg side
slower, on a length and defended to the off side
quicker one, shorter, wider and the batsman wanted to cut it hard, misses the outside edge
gets it off the middle, hits towards long-on but the fielder from short cover runs across to stop it
from round the stumps, on the off stump, bit of turn away and he opens the face of the bat, does not get too much pace on it
shorter on the off and he cuts it to point who is at the edge of the circle
drifts it down the leg side and he taps it away to square-leg for a single
short of length on the off stump and driven down the ground for a single
outside the off and fuller and he goes for a sweep, hits it well too, but goes straight to the square-leg fielder

poor shot, gone, caught! this was on the off stump and turning away but the existence of the Powerplay overs does this to a lot of 'em, the batsman wanted to be aggressive, went for the sweep and the top-edge goes high and easy for the point fielder
fuller on the pads and flicked away to the square-leg region for a single
quicker on the off and moves away from the batsman, beats the outside edge
on his pads, tapped away to square-leg
whoa! quicker on the middle, seemed to be darting in and it suddenly turns away from the right-hander, beaten!
shorter this time and turning away again, beats the outside edge yet again
finds the outside edge of the bat this time and it falls short of the slip fielder to end an excellent over
fuller and flatter on the off stump and driven down the ground for a single
round the stumps and on the middle, defended back
continues his middle-stump line, pushed back to the bowler
it is fuller on the off stump and he defends it well, on the front foot
shorter, quicker and lot of turn, he dabs at it in an attempt to get it through the backward point but goes straight to the fielder
goes down the track but is beaten, wisely decide not to take the single
flatter on the middle, and still there is some turn, he is on his back foot and defends it to the leg side
it is outside the off and driven down to long-on for a single

gone, stumped off the second attempt! checking for a no-ball, and to me that looks like he had some portion behind the crease from one of the square-on cameras and quite different from the other angle...it was outside the off, beats the edge and goes for the stumping as he sees the batsman out of his crease, misses it but is alert enough to whip it off the second time round. Given out.
on the off stump and defended back to the bowler
huge back-lift and presses forward, tapped to the off side
short of length and pushed to the covers, to end an excellent over from Narine
fuller on the off stump and driven through the covers for a couple of runs
on the middle stump, spinning away and defended to the leg side
tucked away to the square-leg region and the keeper has to rush towards it but they are able to get across for a run
shorter, slower and on the off and he wants to cut it away, does not time it too well
but this time he does get the timing right, it was shorter again and he goes hard at it, gets it off the middle too as it rushes off into the gap between point and backward point
gets the line back to the middle, the length back to fuller and the batsman defends it back
outside the off and fuller, pats it to the covers for a single
outside the off stump, length ball and that spins hard and away, beats the outside edge
on the off and he tries to work it away to the leg side, the leading edge goes to the point fielder
bowls within the stumps, hits the pads and there is an appeal for an lbw but was too far forward there, keeper rushes in front to catch it and does a good job too but it is off his pad and pad alone.
flatter on the middle stump but Gazi is able to defend it on the back foot, and well
that is lot of turn but very well played there, he brings the bat down in an angle to counter the turn and play it away through the slips for a four
a very slow ball on the off stump and he tucks it gently to the leg side for a single
goes down the track and wants to have a big heave at it, misses the outside edge
slower one on the off and tucks away to fine-leg for a single
down the leg side and leaves it alone for a wide, Sammy's in a bad shape walking back to his run-up and sending down a wide is the last thing he wants!
on the middle and shorter and slightly quicker too, defended back to the bowler
quicker on the middle, plays it to short fine-leg for a quick single
on the middle, quicker and he wants to reverse paddle, gets it off well but to the short third-man fielder
quicker on the middle and brings his bat down to play it to the leg side
full-toss on the pads, flicked away to deep square-leg for a single
fuller on to the bat and driven down to long-on for a single
fuller and driven to long-on for a single
goes down the track to try and whack it over the mid-off, fails to get any elevation as he is forced to drive it to that fielder, not for runs
slower on the off stump and that is neatly played away to deep square-leg for a single
that is very short but it is just the lack of pace that spoils the timing, gets it to deep square-leg for a single
short of length and tucked away to short fine-leg for a single
slower one and he has to check his drive, gets an inside edge and it loops up in the air, flies off to long-on for a single
another one that lacks in pace, driven to deep square-leg for a single
short of length and quicker this time, taps it to the leg side and wants to go for a single but Sammy, that injury notwithstanding, is quick off the blocks and rushes to prevent the run
poor, poor start, it was quick and down the leg side, plays it with the spin, swept to the fine-leg for a four!
outside the off, nudges it to the point region for a single that gets him to a vital fifty, well played
shorter and tucked away to fine-leg for a single
on the off stump and taps it away to the leg side for a single
turn from outside the off stump and into the batsman, he defends back to the bowler
goes down the track and hits it hard, misfielded by Gayle at short cover and they are able to cross over for a single by the time the mid-off fielder tidies up
short of length on middle and taps it to mid-wicket for a single, the bowler has to run across to field
flick hit away to wide long-on for a single, hit well but not really in the gap there
edged and dropped! that was coming into the bat, he drove at it and gets an outside edge, Thomas was late in getting across there and while he flings himself to the left, he has dropped it
on the off stump and defended to the off side
goes down the track, it is a fuller ball and tries to cramp him, can get it only up to long-on
gone, caught at mid-off this time! it was fuller on the off and they are now going for runs, this is hit well but cannot beat the mid-off fielder, who takes it well on his right
swept away to the backward square-leg fence for a four, Gazi's getting a bit of batting form here
short of length and a bit of spin back into the batsman, tried to cut it but gets nowhere close to the gap
turn from length again, away from the batsman and beats the outside the edge
short of length and this one turns back into the bat, pulled away but to the fielder at deep square-leg for a single
on the middle, quicker and a bit of turn away, leaves it all alone!
this is short and so wide down the leg side that not too many would have got to them. Barring the wicket-keeper that is...
shorter and Narine is pulled away for a single to deep square-leg for a single
short of length and pulled away to long-on for a single
fuller on the middle and he wants to hit it over mid-wicket, bit of an inside edge for a single
slower on the pads and he gets into an awkward position, hits it high but falls just short of the long-on fielder
goes down the track and thwacks it through the extra-cover region for a four, a very good shot, did not try to hit it in the air
drifts down the leg side and he wants to flick it away, hits his pads and goes to the off
goes for another big slog, gets a top edge and it spoons up high in the air for the short cover to get under it and take a simple catch
on the middle stump, but too full for it to turn and he defends it on the front foot
outside the off and pulls the length back, turns back into the batsman, pushes it to the off side to get away from strike
goes for a hoick but the ball turns away, misses the outside edge
shorter and punched down the ground, gets a single and the new man wanted a second as well, but is sent back
carrom-ball and beaten by it going away, it was short of length too
quicker from Narine and he is able to get the bat down to hit it to mid-off, wants the single but is quickly sent back by Gazi
slower, outside the off and smashed straight to the extra-cover fielder, caught easily

inn2.comm: outside the off, bit of turn away and left alone by Gayle
another one from round the stumps, outside off and he shoulders arms
quicker and closer to the off stump but Gayle is watchful and leaves it alone
turn! away from the bat! and a lot of it! quickly away from it, Gayle's leaving them all alone
defended on the front foot, this one goes straight on with the arm
shoulders arms to one that is outside the off to end the first over, a maiden!
whoa, yorker length and swinging into the batsman, on the middle and gets his feet away, taps it back to the bowler
outside the off stump and the batsman is watchful, lets it go through to the keeper
this is a poor ball, on his pads and that has been whipped away over square-leg for a four, West Indies are away
gets his line back to outside the off stump and Powell is back to leaving them alone, the keeper collects
this is wide outside the off, Powell has nothing to do with it, the bowler is lucky to get away with the umpire not calling it wide
maintaining that line outside the off, shorter this time and Powell is able to cut it away to third-man for a single
continues the same process, round the stumps, outside the off and left alone
closer to the stumps, length ball and defended
fuller and on the off stump, driven to short cover
shot, inside out for a six! Powell uses his feet this time, comes down and hits it over wide long-off for a six!
outside the off and lets it go through to the keeper
fuller and on the off stump, drives it through to the cover fielder, who makes a sprawling dive to field it

swing away from the bat, a quick ball too and it seems to have missed the outside edge of the bat, but there is a huge appeal from the keeper and the bowler, the umpire does not join in the celebrations.
short of length outside the off stump and Gayle wanted to fiddle at it before getting his bat away, beaten outside the off
and this one darts back into the bat, he was shaping to cut it but the in-dip makes him check his shot
short of length, he wants to cut it through the covers but gets it only to short cover, Gayle's tenth ball for no run
finally, some runs for Gayle, four of them, outside the off and the batsman was backing away, gets it into the gap and once he had done that there was no stopping the ball

edged and gone! Four and out! It was pitched up but it was a slower one, it gripped on the surface and despite Gayle taking his bottom hand off, it takes the outside edge through to the wicket-keeper. Rahim dives to his left to take a good catch.
outside the off, he goes back and pushes it to the covers but the short cover fields it
quicker and no turn this one, comes in with the arm, taps away to square-leg for a single
fuller on the off stump and driven forcefully down the ground, the mid-off comes around to field it, by which time he is able to get off for a single
shorter and it spins away, he is on the back foot and defends in front of him
quicker and comes in with the arm from round the stumps, defended to the leg side
short of length and pulled away by Powell, Gazi had almost stopped in his run-up right before releasing the ball, much like how Shoaib Malik or R Ashwin do, only a single
outside the off and he flays at it, but manages to get it only to the point fielder
short and comes on rather quickly at the left-hander, he was going for the pull but gets it high on the bat and without the timing he needed, can get it away only for a single
outside the off stump, short of length and bit of nip away, Samuels is on the back foot and punches it to the off side
jaffa! that was on the off and angling in before pitching and going away, slightly outside the off stump and Samuels almost edges it through to the keeper

class, smacks to the fence for four! this was outside the off stump and was short too, Samuels is quickly on to his back foot and crashes it through the covers for a four, Mash isn't happy with himself.
edged and through the gap between the wide slip and gully, it was outside the off, quick and Samuels fiddles at it, goes to third-man
over the wicket, short of length, pushed to the covers
slower in the air but within the stumps, pushed to the leg side
short and that has been smashed away to the deep cover fence for a four, that was the quickest I have seen it being hit today!
and again, the bowler adjusts his length to bowling it much fuller than the previous one and Samuels is waiting, drills it through extra-cover for another four
fuller but closer to the stumps and Samuels defends to the off side
this is fully pitched up and Samuels was going after it, gets a bit of an inside edge that goes to short fine-leg but not for runs
short of length, outside the off and he was able to open the face of the bat through to third-man
what do we have here, this was going down the leg-side and seemed to have missed everything through to the fence, including the batsman and the keeper, but the umpire has called it a dead ball!
outside the off, bit of extra bounce at pace, and the batsman is up on his feet and punches it through gully, was in the air and Mahmudullah even got a hand to it, but very difficult to catch those
outside the off stump and he lets it go through to the keeper
edged and for four! he is going after them alright, it gave him some room and Samuels has flayed at it, there was a wide slip in place but it goes over him and the ball races away to the fence
on a length outside the off and Samuels opens the face of the bat through to third-man for a single
short of length, outside the off and Samuels is having none of it, crashes it through the covers for a four!
another one outside the off, wide enough to unleash the cut, but mistimes it
another one edged after he wants to flay at it, was outside the off and quick, short of length too and he is able to get it through the gully region
on his pads and Powell taps it to short mid-wicket
on the off stump, fuller and driven to mid-off, he is exuding calmness here unlike his partner
a shuffle on to the back foot, was on his pads and he tries to flick it away, hits his pads to short fine-leg
short of length and Samuels isn't going to stop, goes for a pull, but does not hit the middle of the bat, pops towards the leg side
outside the off stump, bit of deviation away from the off and defended to the off side
short, wide, and Jayasuriya will be happy with those slashes, he is going after each one of them outside the off stump which is even slightly short of length, over the cover for four
gosh, that rises from length, was around the off stump and suddenly comes up for Samuels who takes his bottom hand off
jags back you beauty! Samuels was shaping to cut it again and it is a roll over the ball that pitches and spins into the batsman, his bat is a mile away and hits his pads
short of length, slower too and he pulls it away to deep square-leg for a single
short of length and he is on his back foot and punches it to the covers, fielded well to his right by Nasir Hossain
short of length from Rubel and he swivels around to pull it away to in front of square-leg for a couple
short of length, nudges it to square-leg for a single
bouncer from Rubel but it bounces way over the batsman, who has gone under, wide called by the ump
slower one outside the off and he has pushed it to the off side
bowls it from wide of the crease and it angles back into Samuels who wants to cut it but is hurried into defending it
slower and he opens the face of the bat and allows it to come on, single to the right of gully
round the stumps and defended to the off side to one on the middle stump
short, wide and cut away to deep cover for a single
slower, on the off, he is on the back foot and defends it to the leg side
outside the off and floated up, nudged it to the leg side for a single
round the stumps and angles in, defended to the off side
it is outside the off and without any spin there, goes for a cut but straight to the backward point fielder
turn and beats him! comes in from round the stumps and then spins away from the left-hander, beats the outside edge
again on his back foot, wants to play to the leg side but it is quicker and without turn
outside the off and very full, Samuels is not going to miss out on that one, he crunches it through the covers and to make it better for him, he gets it into the gap too, a din of silence
immediately shortens the length and that is tapped away to the square-leg fielder
fuller and driven to mid-on, not for a run though
quicker on his pads and it turns hard, almost surprising the now well-set Samuels, despite all the talks of dew, the ball hasn't stopped turning
outside the off stump and neatly placed to the off side for a single, doing a smart job here is Powell
from round the stumps, coming into the batsman before turning and making him think about his shot
slower in the air and there is that turn yet again, makes Samuels defend hurriedly
this is very short and despite the turn, Samuels latches on to it rather well, cuts it through cover for a four!
defended this time to the leg side
whoa, turn and almost an edge, it has not stopped turning and every now and then the bowlers are getting them to skid past the outside half of the bat
big shout for caught-behind but not-out given! turning away from the left-hander and misses the outside edge, Rahim appealed but the umpire rightly gives it not-out
goes down the pitch but it is quicker and he defends it
goes down the track and drives it this time to long-on for a single
on the off stump and turning into the batsman, who was pushing forward, hits his pads and there is a stifled appeal
gosh, that is some turn, almost Muralitharanesque, outside the off and spins in miles, beats the cut shot
the turn works against the bowler this time as it goes down the leg side for a wide
shorter and Samuels is able to stifle the spin and cut it through the covers for a couple of runs
full-toss and he comes down the track to hit it through the leg side, goes to deep square-leg for a single
short from Razzaq, very short in fact and Samuels goes back and smashes it through mid-wicket, the long-on fielder rushed to his right but does not dive and it goes away to the fence
outside the off and he leaves it alone, wow!
slower and on the middle and Samuels is on the back foot, but the lack of turn beats his shot
ripper! it is on the middle and superbly turns away from the bat, how does he keep missing so many outside edges!
poor ball to follow up, short and wide and cut hard but straight to deep point to take him to 49
outside the off and still that spin into the batsman, who defends it on the front foot
quicker on the middle, no spin and he taps it back to the bowler
on the middle and turning into the batsman, there is some sharp spin but he is able to get over it and flicks it to the deep fielder for a single to get to his 50
round the stumps, outside the off and turning further away, misses the outside edge of the bat, again.
goes down the track, the bowler sees that and pushes it into the batsman and he is still able to clip it over mid-wicket for a four, good shot
shorter this time and it is cut away to deep point for a single
goes for a sweep this time to a ball pitched up and misses, hits the pads
he pitches it short and gets the turn he desires but he is not getting wickets from balls those short, easily played away to the leg side for a single
and now a poor line from Razzaq, drifts down the leg side, clips it away to backward square-leg for a couple
goes down the pitch but misses it, or at least misses the middle of the bat, hits the gloves and rolls down the ground down to fine-leg, they are able to come back for the third
quicker from round the stumps, he is on the back foot and wants to tap it away, hits the pads
shorter, outside the off and cut to the point fielder
outside the off from round the stumps and turn and bounce! beats the outside edge of the bat.
another one that turns away from the bat, he is able to guide it through backward point for a couple of runs
flights it up to the bat, on the middle stump and tapped down the ground for a single
shorter from the bowler and easily tucked away to the leg side for a single
drifts down the leg side and played away to the onside for a single
from round the stumps, and drifts into the pads, misses the flick and hits the pads, there is a loud appeal that follows but the umpire isn't interested
huge, huge appeal for lbw, not given! this was from round the stumps and Samuels is on the back foot, misses the shot and hits the pads, but may have been pitching outside
tapped away to the leg side to one from round the stumps
quicker, an arm ball and Samuels wants to defend at it, misses it by a mile and it hits the pads, they are away for a leg-bye
goes back to this one, which is not full enough and tucks it around the corner
flighted up to Samuels, who brings his bat and pad together and defends it back
quicker and Samuels is on his back foot in an attempt to flick it away but cannot get a bat on it
and that vicious turn from round the stumps continues, but this is a tad short and easily cut away to point for a single
flighted up to the bat and Samuels is beaten again, hits the pads but no appeal for an lbw this time
very quick and turn to go with it as well, Samuels is on the back foot but struggles to put his bat on it
shorter, no turn and Samuels could have tucked it around for a single, hits it straight to the fielder
poor ball, a release ball from the bowler, short, wide, no turn, and Samuels is quickly on to the back foot, latches on to it well, through the point for a four
fuller on the off and Samuels goes for a drive, misses the outside edge of the bat, five off the over
goes for the sweep but the timing is defeated and he gets a bit of a glove, but Rahim cannot get close enough to it
slower outside the off and punched to the off side for a single
slower through the air, drifts in and then spins away, but the tale of the innings, no edge!
quicker, the arm ball and Samuels is on the back foot, had he missed that he would have been out, lbw, just gets his bat down in time
too short that and Samuels has gone back to smack it over mid-wicket for a four
slower outside the off and lets it go through to the keeper
goes down the track and hits it over mid-wicket in the air, for a four! it was more of a short-arm jab
fuller from round the stumps and driven back to the bowler

huge appeal for lbw, he was going back to cut it but it kept very low, seems to have hit the bat and pad both and would have been very difficult for the umpire to decide which one was first! the ball rolls over to third-man and the fielder seems to have done a good job in saving the four
fuller on the off stumps and driven down the ground for a single
outside the off stump and left all alone by the left-hander
round arm, he is still banked on his back foot and punches it back
round the stumps, arm ball and he was expecting it to turn and went for a cut, misses
shorter and he can go on to the back foot and defend
more air given this time and he pushes it to the leg side, not for any runs
quicker one on the off stump, pushes it to the off side
well bowled, fuller, on the stumps and he takes his front foot out and defends
outside the off and fuller, driven to the cover fielder who fumbles and they get a single
flatter, straighter and defended back to the bowler
that is wide down the leg stump and he goes for a pull, and while he misses it gets the team a run that brings up their 100-run stand

whoa, what turn yet again! it comes in from outside the off, Samuels is playing off the front foot and it hits the pad and floats up, Rahim runs after it to the leg side and jumps in front to go for the catch, misses it. Wasn't coming off the bat though
defended off the front foot to the off side
plays it to the off side for a single
driven down the ground for a single, that was a tad short
goes down the track and caresses it through the covers for a four, excellent timing to get his fourth boundary.
down the pitch yet again, gets to the pitch of the ball and drills it through the covers, Tamim Iqbal does a good job getting to it from long-off and restricts it to two
fuller on the off stump, driven to long-on for a single
changes the length, shorter this time and he is able to tuck it away to the leg side
fuller on the middle stump and Samuels, who has gone relatively quiet, pushes it to the leg side, not for a run though
shorter and he continues to play it from the back foot and taps it to the leg side
round the stumps, quicker into the bat, flicked away to the square-leg region for a single
on the off stump, shorter and Marlon punches it to the point region

down the wicket and stumped! That is end of that, finally something goes right for the home team! this was from round the stumps and angling in, the batsman goes down the track to loft him over the top but misses the spin and is easily stumped by Rahim
on his pads, fuller, driven to mid-on by the new man
outside the off and driven to the off side for no run
on the middle stump and driven to the leg side, not for runs though
short of length, on the middle and Samuels, who has gone quiet, pushed it to the mid-wicket region
pushes it to the leg side, but to the fielder at square-leg
driven to the off side, fuller on the off but suddenly he cannot pierce the gap!
shorter and spinning into the batsman, Samuels is only able to tuck it away to square-leg
good bowling this, fuller and Samuels continues to find fielders, and square-leg seems his favourite area
would you believe it, it is a maiden! shorter and turning in, tries to work it into the gap but its the pads
poor bowling this down the leg and its gone away for five wides! went for the sweep did Bravo, which could have blinded the keeper too
shorter and whoa, some turn that, stops on the batsman too and he checks the shot, almost spoons it to the fielder at cover
slower and not up to the bat, he plays off the back foot
this is a lot of turn and surprising that the turn's still there despite the dew, Samuels is unable to hit the middle of the bat
finally a run for Samuels, that's a long time coming, manages to get a gap on the leg side for a single
poor, poor effort at the deep square-leg region, on his pads and he unleashes the on-drive, straight to the deep square-leg fielder, Mashrafe who lets it go through his hands!
down the leg side and he attempts a sweep, misses and it is a wide
gets his line right, on the off stump and turning away, beats the outside edge
fuller and driven down the ground to long-on for a single
short of length, and some extra bounce from round the stumps, wants to play it through the covers but misses the outside edge
fuller and defended off the front foot to the off side
shorter and Bravo comes on to the front foot, defended to the off side

edged and dropped! so when the edges do come, they drop them! it was a quicker one and he went on to the back foot and attempted a cut, it was travelling quickly but the slip fielder should have caught it, Mahmudullah the offender
fuller and given some air, defended to the leg side after it looked like he wanted to go for a slog sweep there
outside the off, very short and cut away to the deep point region for a single
goes for the sweep, but the slowness of the delivery beats him, misses the outside edge
repeat the phrase of the day for me, misses the outside edge, and through to the keeper yet again
whoa, misses the outside edge but this one hits the back pad, appeal for an lbw, but the ump gives it not-out, very close that!
outside the off stump and normal business resumes as the outside edge is missed again
on the off stump and defended by the batsman
fuller on the middle stump and pushed back to the bowler
goes down the track and defends it back to the bowler
shorter and he goes for a cut, gets it to the deep point area for a single
round the stumps, fuller and defended on the front foot
fuller on the off stump, driven down the ground for a single
very short and Samuels was going forward before leaning back and cutting away for a couple of runs
goes for the sweep and it takes the top edge, flies away behind short fine-leg for a couple of runs.
defended to the off side to one fuller but quicker too
a poor ball, released it a tad early I thought, spins into the bat but it is short and goes down the leg side for a wide
another one that's very short and this time Samuels gets some bat on it, a lot of bat on it as it is pulled away to the backward square-leg boundary
very short here, he rocks back and hits it hard to deep square-leg
round the stumps and fuller, he comes forward and defends
this time he gets an edge after all, falls just short of the slip fielder
short of length and punched to the square-leg region
outside the off stump, and no turn this time, pushes it in the gap in the covers for a single
very, very short and a very, very good shot from Bravo! Whacked over mid-wicket for a four and immediately wipes off the dew from the ball

top-edge and taken! he was looking to turn that one to the leg side, hits it across the line to one that is fuller, takes a bit of a leading-cum-top edge and flies off to the backward point fielder, who takes a simple catch
short of length and off-spin there, plays it from the back foot, bit of a misfield allows them a single
on the middle stump, short of length and pushed down the ground for a single
short and Samuels goes back and pulls it to Naeem Islam at backward square-leg, misfields it and the fielder from deep square-leg has to run across to field it
shorter, cuts it away to the off side for a single
short of length and turning back into the batsman, he was going for a cut but mistimes it
quicker on the off stump and he goes on to the back foot and defends it with bat and pad close together
short of length and he goes back, knocks it down the ground for a single
short of length, cut away to deep point for a single, was slower in the air that one
pitched right up to the bat and drilled away by the batsman to mid-on
on the leg stump line, flicked away to deep square-leg for a single
outside the off stump, fuller and defended to the off side
quicker on the middle from round the stumps, defended back to the bowler
he is keeping them up to the bat and for now Smith hasn't unleashed that slog sweep
spin and bounce, turning away from the batsman and beats the outside edge, Rahim was beginning to get excited but without too much of a reason
short of length on the middle stump, turning down the leg side for a wide
short of length, cuts it away to short cover, to the fielder
fuller on the pads, flicked away to square-leg for a single
pitched right up to the bat on the off stump, driven down the ground for a single to long-on
on the middle and spinning into him, tries to play it through the on-side but gets a leading edge, just away from the short cover fielder
quicker, shorter, not turn on this one, attempted the cut but misses
on the off stump and driven to the off side
drifts ever so slightly on to his pads and he has pushed it to long-on for a single
short of length and cut away to the deep point for a single

so it is taking me to talk up the West Indian chances for Bangladesh to get the wickets, this was on the off stump, turning away and Smith was trying to jab it over the top, gets a bit of an outside edge that goes high but not long, the long-on fielder takes an absolute dolly!
that is way down the leg side and Samuels stretches forward, gets bit of a bat there and goes fine for a four down the leg-side
fuller on the off stump and defended
tries to go to the pitch of the ball in a bid to defend it, hits the front pad and there is an appeal but he was way forward
fuller and driven down the ground for a single
outside the off and defended to the off side
short and wide, he tries to cut it away in anger, but goes on the bounce to the fielder in the circle
short of length and he pushes it to the square-leg region, wants a single but the non-striker shouts a loud no.
fuller on the middle stump and driven down to long-on for a single
turning, and a lot! on the off stump line from round the stumps and going away, beats the outside edge
so this is what happens when it does take the edge, it is played through the slips and it rushes through to the fence for four, despite that valiant effort from Gazi
outside the off, fuller and he tries to carve it through the covers but goes straight to the point fielder
flights it up and Samuels feels a tad tempted, but brings his bat down in time, gets an inside edge to square-leg for a single

bowled him, that's a ripper! no it does not turn at all, not an inch! it was a straighter one, and Pollard was playing for the turn that he would have seen all this while, sneaks it between the bat and pad and the castle is rattled!
quicker, within the stumps and Thomas defends it back to the bowler, to end an excellent spell.
short of length, outside the off and cut away but mistimed, straight to point
chops away to the deep point region for a couple of runs, it was outside the off stump and the width allows him to go for it
whoa, almost out! it was short, wide, and it seems to have gone straight to point, but it looks like it went to him on the bounce, nervous moments here for the West Indian side
on the back foot, defends at it and is off for a quick single, the throw from point is wild and nowhere near the stumps at the striker's end, almost hits the batsman
short of length, within the stumps and defended carefully by the new man
middle stump line and he pushes it to mid-on, they are off for a quick single
round the stumps, turning away, goes for a drive, beaten
slower again and beats the outside edge yet again
fuller on the middle and driven down the ground for a single
edged and dropped! that was tossed up and Samuels goes for a drive, gets an outside edge and it carries to the right of the slip fielder, Mashrafe Mortaza and he spills it!
driven through the covers for a single to take him to 97
fuller and driven through the covers for a single
on the off stump, short of length and punches back to the bowler, but not for runs
another one which is bowled within the stumps, fuller as well and Thomas defends well
short of length this as a change, he is on the back foot and swivels across to play it to deep square-leg for a single
pitched right up, slower and Samuels has only managed to get it to short cover, and again, not for runs, the momentum's shifting
slower one but bit of width provided for Samuels, who punches it to the right of the deep cover fielder, they are able to come back for two
short of length and gets back to bowling 'em within the stumps, defended to the left of the bowler
turn and square! where is that dew? turn and bounce and beats the outside edge of the bat
defended on the front foot, but again, not for runs
third dot in a row, edged short of the slips, but the batsman will now be in pressure
aww! that was fuller and driven back to the bowler, should have been fielded, gets away for a single in the process

just in and that is a century! driven to backward point and they are away for a single, but that is a good throw from Gazi and Rahim whips the bails away...third umpire called. Thomas was diving at the striker's end and while his bat was in when the bails came off, there is a chance that the bat was in the air at the point when the bails were removed. A very tough call one way or the other, more so given the situation of the game. Given not-out in the end to get Samuels his century.
on the off stump, fuller and would you believe it, Thomas defends and that ends an over that has cost 'em only two!
now that he has his 100, and now that the required-rate's going up, he goes for the cut, gets bit of an outside edge and rushes away to the fine third-man for a four
fuller and that is two in two! drilled through the covers for a four, this has been one of the most matured innings you would see on a turning track
three in three! and is this the end of the game? it was fuller and he gives himself room and drives it through the mid-wicket region for a four!

whoa, whoa whoa! Samuels has turned it on so well this over, it was pitched right up to the bat and slower, Samuels was waiting, he picks it up and smacks it over long-on for a six, game, set and match I would believe.
wild swing this time, beaten but misses the stumps, goes through to the keeper
and again, fuller, faster and it goes off the bat really quickly as well, and over the long-off fence for a six! 24 off the over takes West Indies to within 10 runs of their first win this series
driven down the ground for a single to long-off
opens the face of the bat and guides it through off side for a single
defended on the front foot and back to the bowler
fuller from round the stumps and Thomas pats it to the off side
flighted ball and it is easily drilled through the covers for a single
round the stumps, and pitched up to the bat, Samuels covers the spin and drives it through for a single
pulled and caught! short of length and Samuels gives himself room, wants to pull it away, but the top edge goes up and straight into the hands of the fielder at square-leg!
short of length outside the off and cut away to deep point for a single
outside the off and fuller, defended it back to the bowler
short of length and flicked away with typically Caribbean flair to fine-leg for a single
outside the off and he shoulders arms
edged and four! that was outside the off stump, he went out to fiddle at it, got an edge and flies between the keeper and the slip, goes to the fence to win West Indies the game
